  "body": "<!--NOTE: -->\r\n<!--- General questions should go to the discord chat instead of the issue tracker.-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nTo create a public key BLS spec requires first validate the public key bytes. \r\nTo validate the input bytes [fromBytes](https://github.com/ChainSafe/bls/blob/master/src/blst/publicKey.ts#L12) must be called as `fromBytes(bytes, type, true)`.\r\n\r\nThe following fragments call fromBytes without validation:\r\n- https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/master/packages/lodestar/src/chain/bls/multithread/worker.ts#L39\r\n- https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/master/packages/lodestar/src/chain/bls/multithread/worker.ts#L53\r\n- https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/88e1280632f06891fe1dcd210cf3272609c7729f/packages/light-client/src/utils/utils.ts#L65\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nThe `fromBytes` function should be called with validate = true\r\n\r\n**Steps to Reproduce**\r\n\r\n<!--Steps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Go to '...'\r\n2. Click on '....'\r\n3. Scroll down to '....'\r\n4. See error\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Screenshots**\r\n\r\n<!--If applicable, add screenshots to help explain your problem.-->\r\n\r\n**Desktop (please complete the following information):**\r\n\r\n- OS: <!--[e.g. ubuntu, OSX High Siera]-->\r\n- Version: <!--[e.g. 22]-->\r\n- Branch: <!--[Master]-->\r\n- Commit hash: <!--[e8232]-->\r\n",
